<div style="float: left; white-space: pre; line-height: 1; background: #FFFFFF; "><span class="sc0">Title:          Spring and Inner class.
Description:    This blog will tell how to instantiate inner class and definition of inner class in spring xml configuration.



Spring can define bean for nested classes. Here we will see how we can define beans for inner classes (nested classes.) This does not include local classes or annymous classes.
1.  Static nested classes.
Inner nested classes are those classes which are defined as static within enclosing class.
Java  Outer class and Inner class:
[sourcecode language="java"]
package co.uk.javavm.spring.core.inner;

public class OuterClass {
    private String name;
    public String getName() {
        return name;
    }
    public void setName(String name) {
        this.name = name;
    }
    //Public static inner class
    public static class InnerClass {
        private String familyName;

        public String getFamilyName() {
            return familyName;
        }

        public void setFamilyName(String familyName) {
            this.familyName = familyName;
        }
    }
}
[/sourcecode]
Above java code has an inner public static class Inner with property familyName. Inner class has to be public to define bean of it


keywords:
spring static inner method example,spring instance factory method example,spring example,spring bean definition,spring way of bean definition,spring bean definition example,spring factoy method, spring how to define beans,spring tutorial
